	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=123865><span id= >raiaxa</span></a><br><span id=notbold>6 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.66]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Well since half the posts here are about ppls saying that this is equal to 60 bard, bard can beat easily, blah blah blah, let me dispel the myths with some numbers.&nbsp;&nbsp;Ornate chain=AAXP pally and SK horses.  The movement % increase is 85%.  A bard SINGING selo's at 60 without a drum or epic increases movement 75%.  A Bard using a regular (non-magical) drum or epic gets 105%, easily outpacing this bridle. So if he's just singing it or oddly doesnt have his epic yet you'll outrun him.  The other 99% of the time he'll outrun you.  Still, not bad speed for a non-movement oriented hybrid.<br><br>As for the other classes, fastest druid spell Form of the Hunter increases movement by 70%.  You can outrun them.  Shamans' is Spirit of Scale which is also 70% but goes away if they get into combat.  Smoke 'em too. So you become the 2nd fastest in the game.  Nuff said.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
